text: Interstate 105 (I-105), also called the Glenn Anderson Freeway, is an Interstate Highway in Los Angeles County, California. It is a short spur of the Interstate 5. It goes from the Interstate 605 west to California State Route 1 at Los Angeles International Airport. The highway runs south of Los Angeles and north of Compton in an east-west direction. It is about long. When it first opened, it was called the Century Freeway. ==Exits== ==References== Category:Interstate Highways Category:Los Angeles County, California Category:Roads in California
